{
  "stem": "7739.3",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And he caned me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "It wasn't so bad.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] And we were there until January.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] We could steal the odd handful of oats.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "No more sugar beets.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And one day, there was a bombing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "The airplanes came, Russian airplanes, and they bombed the camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Outside the camp they had the anti-aircraft guns.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "I hid when the bombs came, when the-- when the-- when the airplanes came, and I hear a bomb drop.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And I got myself-- my head up, and I see they leveled the SS barrack, right next to our barrack.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Outside-- theirs was outside of the wires, ours was inside.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "But the SS men were in the bunkers.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "There was no one in the barrack there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "Two days later, we were-- we were assembled together with the cattle and the horses, allowed to take a blanket.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "January, 1945.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "Marched out of the camp.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "We were marched out of the camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "When we hit the main road, you looked around.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "You would think the whole world is marching.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "We marched out with the cattle.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "Our guards rode the horses.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "We were marching.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And we marched, and we marched, and we marched.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And we marched for 100 miles.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "We marched from Auschwitz to the city of Breslau, which was in Silesia.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "And so many people died on that march that you couldn't march maybe for 100 meters not to see somebody dead on either side of the road.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "The guards, either they took a disliking to you, or you got slow, or you got just plainly gave up.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "So they shot you, and they got people on both sides of the road.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
